00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:31,000
 Your life begins to look, and it doesn't mean life's easy.

480
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,000
 She hasn't had a baby.

481
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:34,000
 Life's not all perfect.

482
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:39,000
 But on Sunday, this past Sunday, she led, she helped to lead Palm Sunday

483
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:45,000
 gathering for women, and she sang and led worship about the goodness of God.

484
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:49,000
 I mean, you talk about, and she's telling me in tears a couple days ago,

485
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:50,000
 like, God is so good, Tyler.

486
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 God is so good.

487
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:55,000
 I go, man, I want some of that.

488
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:57,000
 And you get that through the fire.

489
00:30:57,000 --> 00:31:00,000
 Don't buy the lie that your suffering's meaningless.

490
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:01,000
 It's not.

491
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:05,000
 It's producing something in you if you will hold on.

492
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:06,000
 That's the first thing.

493
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:09,000
 James says, you want to be able to count it all joy?

494
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:12,000
 You need to see your suffering is producing something.

495
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:14,000
 There's purpose in the pain.

496
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:21,000
 Second thing, quickly, second thing, there's perfection in the process.

497
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:24,000
 There's perfection in the process.

498
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,000
 Let's keep reading.

499
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 Look at verse 4.

500
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:32,000
 He says, "And let steadfastness have its full effect,

501
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:37,000
 that you may be perfect and complete, lacking in nothing."

502
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,000
 Okay, this is a crazy verse.

503
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:40,000
 Think about that.

504
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,000
 Let's read it again.

505
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:43,000
 He says, "So count it all joy and suffering.

506
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:45,000
 It's producing steadfastness," verse 4,

507
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:48,000
 "and let steadfastness have its full effect,

508
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:54,000
 that you may be perfect and complete, lacking in nothing."

509
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:56,000
 So he's saying, as you go through suffering

510
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:59,000
 and God is producing something in you,

511
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:02,000
 you're on the road to perfection.

512
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:03,000
 So you go, whoa, whoa, perfect?

513
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:05,000
 Nobody's perfect.

514
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:09,000
 This word in Greek for perfect is the word teleos,

515
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:12,000
 which means whole or mature.

516
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:14,000
 He's going, as you go through suffering,

517
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:17,000
 you're becoming a whole person.

518
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:18,000
 I love what Tim Mackey says.

519
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:19,000
 We have it on the screen.

520
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:22,000
 He says, "In biblical Hebrew and Greek,

521
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:25,000
 this word teleos refers to wholeness.

522
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:28,000
 It means living a completely integrated life

523
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:31,000
 where your actions are always consistent

524
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:34,000
 with the values and belief that you received from Jesus."

525
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:38,000
 He said, "Most of us actually live as fractured people

526
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:41,000
 with big inconsistencies in our character.

527
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:44,000
 We are all more compromised than we want to admit.

528
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:49,000
 However, God is on a mission to restore fractured people

529
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:51,000
 and make them whole."

530
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:56,000
 See, God is not just trying to get you through your trial.

531
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:59,000
 He's trying to grow you in the midst of it.

532
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:05,000
 And oftentimes, the great refining moment of our lives

533
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:07,000
 is when we go through a trial, why?

534
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:12,000
 Because adversity introduces you to yourself.

535
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:13,000
 What do I mean by that?

536
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:16,000
 Adversity introduces you to yourself.

537
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:18,000
 I was talking with someone last week,

538
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:20,000
 and I was kind of listening to him,

539
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:24,000
 and he was saying that we live in an age where he says,

540
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:27,000
 he calls it an hour of fragmentation.

541
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:29,000
 He said, "We live in a day and age

542
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:32,000
 where everybody is double-minded."

543
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,000
 I said, "What do you mean?"

544
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:36,000
 He said, "It's the idea of," this is a simple example,

545
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:38,000
 but it's like when you ask someone,

546
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:40,000
 "Hey, do you want to go to this thing?"

547
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:42,000
 And they say, "Oh, well, part of me does,

548
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,000
 and part of me doesn't."

549
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:45,000
 Right? Have you ever done that?

550
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:48,000
 Part of me does, but I don't know, part of me doesn't.

551
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:50,000
 That's the idea of living fragmented.

552
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:53,000
 And that's a simple example, we all do that.

553
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:56,000
 The problem is when you live your whole life,

554
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:58,000
 and every conversation is you're going,

555
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:00,000
 "Should I show up as this person

556
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:02,000
 or should I show up as this person?"

557
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:07,000
 And you begin to wonder, "Who am I really?"

558
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:09,000
 And in the moment of trial,

559
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:13,000
 adversity introduces you to yourself.

560
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:16,000
 You find out who you really are.

561
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:20,000
 And so I'm curious, where is your life fractured?

562
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:23,000
 Where are you living in such a way

563
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:25,000
 where you're showing up as different people

564
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:27,000
 in different environments?

565
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:30,000
 And where's God inviting you to be more whole?

