00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:33,000
 As I'm leaving the church down in Houston,

567
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:36,000
 I'm having a lot of conversations with people, close friends,

568
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:38,000
 as we say our goodbyes.

569
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:42,000
 And one of the things that I do with everybody who's close,

570
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:47,000
 I ask them at the end a really risky question, really risky.

571
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:52,000
 I say, "Hey, what is one thing that you are praying

572
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:55,000
 God grows in me over the next year?"

573
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:58,000
 It's a risky question,

574
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,000
 because people who love you will tell you the truth.

575
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:02,000
 And I've had a couple of people who've loved me

576
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:05,000
 and they've told me the truth, and it's hurt.

577
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:09,000
 And one of the things that I've heard now multiple times,

578
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:11,000
 I just heard it again last week,

579
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:14,000
 is one guy, I sat down, "Hey, what's one thing you want me to,

580
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:16,000
 you're praying God grows in me?"

581
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:17,000
 He goes, "Yeah, Tyler, I'm praying

582
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:19,000
 that you would become more vulnerable

583
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:21,000
 when you go up to Dallas,

584
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:25,000
 that you open up more to your community."

585
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:29,000
 And I'll be honest, when I hear that, it stings,

586
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:32,000
 because I so badly wanna be a vulnerable person.

587
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:36,000
 I don't wanna have anything hidden, I just wanna be real.

588
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:39,000
 And so I'm calling mentors,

589
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:40,000
 I'm meeting with them at their house,

590
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:42,000
 I'm texting different guys every day,

591
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:45,000
 I'm trying to get staff and people in my world

592
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:47,000
 to speak into my life.

593
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:50,000
 And yet, as I really sat with the Lord with that question,

594
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:54,000
 I realized, wow, I actually think part of it's true.

595
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:57,000
 And I remember talking to one guy and he said,

596
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:59,000
 "You know, one problem with you, Tyler,

597
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:01,000
 is you're such a good listener,

598
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:03,000
 you ask a bunch of good questions,

599
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:06,000
 but you never turn it back on yourself."

600
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:08,000
 And I realized, often for me,

601
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:10,000
 I'm thinking about that other person

602
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:12,000
 kind of because I care about them,

603
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:15,000
 but also kind of because I want them to like me,

604
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:17,000
 and I gotta show up, I gotta realize,

605
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:19,000
 who do I need to be in this conversation

606
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:21,000
 so that you like me back?

